A Brief Moment of Revelation


16 Jan 2020 01:15






Here it is, my 5k. This was intended to mostly be about one of the weirder definitions of mystery - specifically,  - but then a regular mystery snuck back in with the idea of Thornettle disappearing without a trace. They're still linked, but I was really expecting this to only be tangentially linked to the theme. Funny how it works out.

Thanks to my reviewers Habitual_Snubnose for loooking this over before posting.

TheHerewithin

Howmysterious


The first mystery is the sacred mystery, under the definition above. It is the mystery of faith, but also the theme of divine enlightenment and things that can only be understood through that lense. This is not a mystery in the typical sense, and has no solution.
The second mystery is what happened to Thornettle. Did he burn to death, get fatally [REDACTED]  in another dimension, join the angels, or has he escaped the UIU/SCP all these years? This is not a mystery that innately has an answer within the article.
The third mystery is what is behind the [REDACTED] s. This has an answer within the SCP and can be solved. Please put any guesses to this in spoilers in the comments.





cameostrivia

randomtidbits


The Department of Anomalous Drugs and Ordinance is said to be severely understaffed. This is because they are only a single man. Many years after this article, something happens to this man, and DADO becomes dado.
The friend from Reed College actually went to Deer College and had done other anomalous drugs before, so the stuff they did with Kollwitz didn't knock their socks off. They just told Kollwitz they went to Reed, which was close enough to the truth.





